::DarkMouse::

She stumbles along.  The fear in her is over riding her logic 
circuits.
"Got to get away from them." she said aloud to herself.
She stopped and leaned against a tree for a moment to catch her 
breath.  "Why? Why? Why?"  She heard a noise behind her and bolted 
again.  She stopped when she came to the edge of a  cliff.  It was 
about 200 feet to the river below.  She stopped right at the 
edge. "Oh boy...wrong way." She backed up from the edge.  She knelt 
down on her knees.
"Oh that would have been a long drop." She swallowed even though her 
throat was dry.  SHe was getting tired and needed to rest.  But she 
knew she had to keep going.  She stood up and walked back the way she 
came.
